---
layout: base.njk
title: false
summary: "Domus Communis Foundation — data sovereignty, sovereign AI, and values-based technology for the common good."
---
<section class="home-intro">
  <p class="home-statement"><strong>Domus Communis Foundation</strong> is a global constellation of nonprofits dedicated to data sovereignty, sovereign AI, and values-based technology that serves humanity rather than the reverse. Guided by Catholic Social Teaching while serving people of all faiths, we connect technologists, civil society, academia, and faith leaders to shape a future where technology serves human dignity, peace, and the common good.</p>
</section>

<section class="home-section home-concepts">
  <h2 class="home-section-heading">Key Concepts</h2>
  <ul class="concept-list">
    <li class="concept">
      <h3 class="concept-title">Data Sovereignty</h3>
      <p class="concept-text">Individuals and entities hold full rights over their data: access, control, sharing, and monetization. Ownership and value stay with the original data creators.</p>
    </li>
    <li class="concept">
      <h3 class="concept-title">Sovereign AI</h3>
      <p class="concept-text">AI architected to act for its human user — aligned to their values, following their commands, so autonomy stays with the person, not a third-party AI agent.</p>
    </li>
    <li class="concept">
      <h3 class="concept-title">Value-Based AI Programming</h3>
      <p class="concept-text">AI designed to carry human values at its core.</p>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p class="home-concepts-more"><a href="/about/">Learn more about our mission →</a></p>
</section>

<section class="home-section home-initiatives">
  <h2 class="home-section-heading"><a href="/initiatives/">Initiatives</a></h2>
  <p class="home-initiatives-lead">Eight programs advancing human-centered technology — across peacebuilding, education, research, regulation, and faith.</p>
  <ul class="initiative-grid">
    <li><a href="/initiatives/">Peace</a></li>
    <li><a href="/initiatives/">Technology</a></li>
    <li><a href="/initiatives/">Academia</a></li>
    <li><a href="/initiatives/">Education</a></li>
    <li><a href="/initiatives/">Mentorship</a></li>
    <li><a href="/initiatives/">Research</a></li>
    <li><a href="/initiatives/">Regulatory</a></li>
    <li><a href="/initiatives/">Theology &amp; Philosophy</a></li>
  </ul>
  <p class="home-initiatives-more"><a href="/initiatives/">See all initiatives →</a></p>
</section>

{% set upcoming = [] %}
{% set past = [] %}
{% for event in collections.events %}
  {% if event.data.date | isPast %}{% set past = (past.push(event), past) %}{% else %}{% set upcoming = (upcoming.push(event), upcoming) %}{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% set featuredEvent = null %}
{% set featuredIsPast = false %}
{% if upcoming.length %}{% set featuredEvent = (upcoming | sort(false, false, "data.date"))[0] %}{% elif past.length %}{% set featuredEvent = (past | sort(true, false, "data.date"))[0] %}{% set featuredIsPast = true %}{% endif %}

{% if featuredEvent %}
<section class="home-section">
  <h2 class="home-section-heading"><a href="/events/">Events</a></h2>
  <ul class="card-list">
    <li class="card">
      <a class="card-link" href="{{ featuredEvent.url }}">
        {% if featuredEvent.data.cardImage %}<div class="card-thumb"><img src="{{ featuredEvent.data.cardImage }}" alt=""></div>{% else %}<div class="card-thumb card-thumb-placeholder"></div>{% endif %}
        <div class="card-text">
          <p class="card-kicker">{% if featuredIsPast %}Recent Event{% else %}Upcoming Event{% endif %}</p>
          <h3 class="card-title">{{ featuredEvent.data.title }}</h3>
          {% if featuredIsPast and featuredEvent.data.summary %}<p class="card-dek">{{ featuredEvent.data.summary }}</p>{% elif featuredEvent.data.subtitle %}<p class="card-dek">{{ featuredEvent.data.subtitle }}</p>{% endif %}
          <p class="card-meta"><time datetime="{{ featuredEvent.data.date | isoDate }}">{{ featuredEvent.data.date | dateDisplay }}</time></p>
        </div>
      </a>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if collections.essays.length %}
<section class="home-section">
  <h2 class="home-section-heading"><a href="/writing/">Writing</a></h2>
  <ul class="card-list">
  {% for essay in (collections.essays | reverse).slice(0, 3) %}
    <li class="card">
      <a class="card-link" href="{{ essay.url }}">
        {% if essay.data.hero %}<div class="card-thumb"><img src="{{ essay.data.hero }}" alt=""></div>{% else %}<div class="card-thumb card-thumb-placeholder"></div>{% endif %}
        <div class="card-text">
          {% if essay.data.category %}<p class="card-kicker">{{ essay.data.category }}</p>{% endif %}
          <h3 class="card-title">{{ essay.data.title }}</h3>
          {% if essay.data.summary %}<p class="card-dek">{{ essay.data.summary }}</p>{% endif %}
          {% if essay.data.date %}<p class="card-meta"><time datetime="{{ essay.data.date | isoDate }}">{{ essay.data.date | dateDisplay }}</time></p>{% endif %}
        </div>
      </a>
    </li>
  {% endfor %}
  </ul>
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if collections.posts.length %}
<section class="home-section">
  <h2 class="home-section-heading"><a href="/newsroom/">Newsroom</a></h2>
  <ul class="home-news">
  {% for post in (collections.posts | reverse).slice(0, 3) %}
    <li class="home-news-item">
      <p class="feed-meta">{% if post.data.date %}<time datetime="{{ post.data.date | isoDate }}">{{ post.data.date | dateDisplay }}</time>{% endif %}</p>
      {% if post.data.title %}<h3 class="home-news-title"><a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a></h3>{% else %}<p class="home-news-untitled"><a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.summary or "Read post →" }}</a></p>{% endif %}
    </li>
  {% endfor %}
  </ul>
</section>
{% endif %}